A photograph of a woman branding a lathi at policemen in riot gear has been linked to the farmers’ protest and shared on social media. A parody Twitter account that goes by the username @Rofl_Kamra shared the image on November 28. The caption made a reference to actor Kangana Ranaut who played the role of Rani Lakshmibai in a movie. It termed her ‘fake’ Jhansi Ki Rani and the woman in the photo as the real warrior queen.
नकली झांसी की रानी को देख चुके तो अब देखो असली झांसी की रानी जो किसान हक के लिए कूद पड़ी है युद्ध के मैदान में…माँ तुझे सलाम…🙏 pic.twitter.com/glJq6ho0gi
— Rofl Kamra 2.0 (@Rofl_Kamra) November 28, 2020
Lawyer Deepika Singh Rajawat and Jharkhand Pradesh Youth Congress also circulated the picture with similar message taking a dig at Ranaut.

National President of Tipu Sultan Party Prof Shaikh Sadeque tweeted the picture as well. Several other Twitter users circulated the image and among the prominent ones were @Rayaan41, @The_vinaydubey and @Kavita_Meena1.

A reverse-image search on Bing led us to a Facebook page that had uploaded the picture in 2016.
Posted by Hyderabad Funny Club on Saturday, 10 September 2016
A Twitter user had shared the image in 2018 however without mentioning where it was shot. He used hashtags related to farmers’ protests.

While Alt News could not establish further details about the image, it clearly does not represent an incident that took place in the ongoing farmers’ protests.
